name: places/ChIJTaXO02YZ2jERMhbMdG-cAw4/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURYMGV6M1VREAE
text:
{'text': "A very beautiful Catholic church.
Large well-maintained grounds, columbarium.
St. Theresa's Church is one of the churches in the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Singapore. Built in 1929, it has been a national monument since 2009.
Today, I did not venture inside the church during the farewell to the deceased.
But you can check out all the information on the website and decide when to visit here. The website has all the detailed information on masses and free admission to the temple.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': 'Very beautiful parish, located a few bus stops away from Outram Park MRT. They did the Angelus and Salve Regina in Latin on an ordinary weekday mass.\n\nThe homily was very insightful and easy to listen to without drifting off', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJTaXO02YZ2jERMhbMdG-cAw4/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNvN2ZUaE53EAE
text: {'text': 'Good and old church that was renovated. One of its kind in SG. Have some stained glass. Aircon is good. Acoustic is good. The current priest was a chancellor so his preaching is true to the word. Hospitality team is also great.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
